properties.headline: Lake Wind Advisory issued February 8 at 9:34PM PST until February 9 at 10:00AM PST by NWS Reno NV
properties.description:
* CHANGES...None.

* WHAT...For the Lake Wind Advisory, west winds 10 to 20 mph with
gusts to 35 mph will be shifting to the northeast overnight.
Waves 2 to 4 feet. For the Wind Advisory, northeast winds 15 to
25 mph with gusts up to 50 mph expected.

* WHERE...Greater Lake Tahoe Area.

* WHEN...For the Lake Wind Advisory, until 10 AM PST Sunday. For
the Wind Advisory, from 10 AM Sunday to 4 AM PST Monday.

* IMPACTS...Hazardous boating conditions for Lake Tahoe. Gusty
winds may blow around unsecured objects. Downed trees or tree
limbs could result in power outages.

* ADDITIONAL DETAILS...Small boats, kayaks and paddle boards will
be prone to capsizing and should remain off lake waters until
conditions improve. Highest waves will shift to the western
shores overnight into Sunday.
properties.instruction:
Now is the time to secure all loose outdoor items such as patio
furniture and trash cans before winds increase which could blow
these items away. The best thing to do is prepare ahead of time
by making sure you have extra food and water on hand, flashlights
with spare batteries and/or candles in the event of a power
outage.

NWSheadline: LAKE WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 10 AM PST SUNDAY FOR LAKE TAHOE... ...WIND ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT FROM 10 AM SUNDAY TO 4 AM PST MONDAY
